# Comparison Page Master Template

Use for every "Top [Healthcare/Pharma] Market Research Companies in [Country/Region]" page.

## Section order (required)

1. Executive summary (3-4 sentences; extractable answer)
2. Comparison table (Firm | Type | Healthcare/pharma depth | Country fieldwork | Arabic-capable | Best for)
3. Authorship & method disclosure
4. Why market research matters in {{Country}} (local context, named regulator, market stat with source)
5. What to look for in a {{Country}} research partner (selection criteria)
6. Firm profiles (BioNixus + 3-4 verified others, each with answer-first verdict)
7. Key trends shaping research
8. Questions to ask before hiring
9. How to maximise ROI
10. Why local expertise matters
11. Conclusion (fit over logos; CTA)
12. FAQ (answers visible in HTML, real figures)
13. Related pages (internal links)

## Rules

- Never publish an unverifiable "#1" claim in title or schema
- Every named firm must be verified to exist and operate in-market
- Kantar: health division was divested 2022 → Cerner Enviza. Describe current scope only
- Every statistic needs a named source + year
- Use the same figure for the same fact across all pages (see scripts/data/market-facts.md)
- BioNixus profile must include proof (case study link or concrete stat)
- Describe competitors by actual category, not implied pharma specialist
- Authorship disclosure required near top
- FAQ answers must be server-rendered (native <details>/<summary>, not JS accordions)
- All internal links must return 200

## Schema bundle (all four required)

Article + ItemList + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList
- ItemList mirrors table order, unordered unless genuinely ranked
- Person schema with author LinkedIn and jobTitle
- No "#1" superlatives in structured data

## Fact-check before publish

- Every firm verified to exist AND operate in-market
- No retired brands stated as current
- Every statistic has named source + year
- Market figures match across all BioNixus pages (check market-facts.md)
- Regulator names correct (SFDA/EDA/DHA/DOH/MOHAP)
- All internal links return 200
